.TH "DFIR-CLI" "1" "Apr 2026" "DFIR Lab" "DFIR CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
dfir-cli-usage - Display locally recorded API usage statistics


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdfir-cli usage [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Display locally recorded API usage statistics including request counts,
credit consumption, and a breakdown by service.

.PP
The period flag controls which billing period to display:
  current   — the current month (default)
  previous  — the previous month
  YYYY-MM   — a specific month (e.g. 2026-03)

.PP
Optionally filter by service (phishing, exposure, enrichment, ai) and limit
the number of top operations shown.

.PP
Usage is built from successful dfir-cli API calls recorded on this machine.
The command does not make a network request.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for usage

.PP
\fB--period\fP="current"
	Billing period: current, previous, or YYYY-MM

.PP
\fB--service\fP=""
	Filter by service: phishing, exposure, enrichment, ai

.PP
\fB--top\fP=10
	Number of top operations to display


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-key\fP=""
	Override API key for this invocation

.PP
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	Override API base URL (default from config)

.PP
\fB-j\fP, \fB--json\fP[=false]
	Shorthand for --output json

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, jsonl, csv

.PP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--profile\fP="default"
	Named config profile

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Minimal output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=1m0s
	HTTP request timeout

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	Show debug information (HTTP requests/responses)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dfir-cli usage
  dfir-cli usage --period previous
  dfir-cli usage --period 2026-01 --service enrichment
  dfir-cli usage --top 5
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdfir-cli(1)\fP
